WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.205
Common Reasoning Trap: Assuming conflict avoidance preserves team harmony, when

00:00:04.205 --> 00:00:08.410
it causally guarantees artificial harmony and stifled innovation. Team dysfunction

00:00:08.410 --> 00:00:12.614
is a predictable causal chain. The absence of trust mathematically

00:00:12.614 --> 00:00:16.819
guarantees the fear of conflict. Without trust, your team will

00:00:16.819 --> 00:00:21.024
not engage in the productive debate required for innovation. Perform

00:00:21.024 --> 00:00:25.229
a critique: Evaluate a hypothetical team that consistently fails to

00:00:25.229 --> 00:00:29.434
commit to strategic decisions, resulting in ambiguity and hesitation. Trace

00:00:29.434 --> 00:00:33.638
this failure back through the causal chain. The lack of

00:00:33.638 --> 00:00:37.843
commitment is a direct symptom of the fear of conflict,

00:00:37.843 --> 00:00:42.048
which itself is rooted in an absence of trust.
